template: Generate one single-sentence plain-English prompt describing a realistic software engineering task in {technical_domain} that includes defining requirements, building components, testing, fixing issues, and deploying to an environment; output only the prompt text under 45 words.
filled_prompt: Generate one single-sentence plain-English prompt describing a realistic software engineering task in mobile app that includes defining requirements, building components, testing, fixing issues, and deploying to an environment; output only the prompt text under 45 words.

message.content: Develop a new user profile editor for our mobile app, defining requirements first, then building components, testing thoroughly, fixing bugs, and finally deploying it to the staging environment.
message.reasoning_content:
Hmm, the user wants a concise single-sentence prompt for a mobile app software engineering task. The task needs to cover the full lifecycle: requirements, building, testing, bug-fixing, and deployment. 

Okay, keeping it under 45 words means every word must count. I can structure it as a direct instruction starting with an action verb. "Develop" covers the initial building phase. "Define requirements first" sets the preliminary step. "Test thoroughly" and "fix bugs" handle the quality assurance cycle. Finally, "deploy to staging" completes the deployment requirement. 

The phrase "a new user profile editor" makes it concrete and realistic for a mobile app context. The sentence flows naturally while hitting all the requested checkpoints.
